                "A woman of the Ancestral South Indian peoples of the peninsular subcontinent (c. 10,000-2000 BCE), lean and weathered, wearing a minimal plant-fibre and soft-hide skirt-wrap, her skin marked with linear ochre body-painting, adorned as the Bhimbetka figures are: many strands of ostrich-eggshell, seed, shell and bone beads, bangles and wrist, arm and elbow bands, knee-bands with tassels, her hair bound up and dressed with shell and seed ornaments. The full-bleed background is the Deccan forager world: tropical deciduous forest and granite hills, a hunted blackbuck and wild boar, a bow with microlith-tipped arrows, ground-stone tools, early millet plots and humped zebu cattle, ochre rock-shelter paintings on a stone face, and a thatched shelter by a fire."),
            ["Sub Saharan African"] = (
                "A man of an ancient Sub-Saharan African foraging people of deep antiquity (one of humanity's oldest lineages, ancestral San-related) — wearing a soft animal-hide kaross slung over one shoulder and strands of ostrich-eggshell beads at his neck and brow, his hair in tight natural coils. The full-bleed background is the ancient African world: golden savanna and bushland under a wide sky, a hunted antelope, a hunter's bow with poison-tipped arrows and a hide quiver, a digging stick and a gourd, ochre-and-white rock-art figures painted on a stone face, scattered flat-topped acacia trees, and a hearth glowing at the mouth of a rock shelter.",
                "A woman of an ancient Sub-Saharan African foraging people of deep antiquity (one of humanity's oldest lineages, ancestral San-related) — wearing a soft animal-hide kaross worn as a cloak (doubling as a carrying-cape) over a beaded front-and-back leather apron, with abundant ostrich-eggshell bead jewellery: a beaded headband, layered neck and chest strands, and bracelets, her hair in tight natural coils. The full-bleed background is the ancient African world: golden savanna and bushland under a wide sky, a hunted antelope, a hunter's bow with poison-tipped arrows and a hide quiver, a gatherer's weighted digging stick and a gourd, ochre-and-white rock-art figures painted on a stone face, scattered flat-topped acacia trees, and a hearth glowing at the mouth of a rock shelter."),
            ["Illyrian (1200 - 250 BC)"] = (
                "A man of the Iron Age western Balkans (c. 1200-250 BCE) in Illyrian battle gear: a white brimless felt pileus cap - a smooth, perfectly egg-shaped solid half-dome holding its shape, with NO folds, creases, wrinkles or drooping tip - fitted snugly over the crown and tilted slightly back; a white knee-length many-pleated fustanella kilt over a woollen tunic with a short cloak, a wide riveted decorated bronze war-belt, and bronze greaves. The full-bleed background is the Illyrian world: the blue Adriatic crowded with fast low-slung lembos galleys packed with oarsmen and warriors, and along the rocky coast only Hellenistic stone cities - white colonnaded temples, a theatre and stone harbour walls - absolutely NO huts, mud-brick or primitive dwellings anywhere, under a bright Mediterranean sky.",
                "A woman of the Iron Age western Balkans (c. 1200-250 BCE) of Illyrian high standing, heavily draped with bronze and amber adornment as on festive days: a long woven woollen dress pinned at both shoulders with large double-spiral spectacle fibulae and Glasinac bow-brooches, belted at the waist, with a draped headcloth veil over coiled braided hair; a bronze diadem, spiral arm- and leg-rings, serpentine pendants and amber and glass bead strands. The full-bleed background is the Illyrian world: the blue Adriatic crowded with fast low-slung lembos galleys packed with oarsmen and warriors, and along the rocky coast only Hellenistic stone cities - white colonnaded temples, a theatre and stone harbour walls - absolutely NO huts, mud-brick or primitive dwellings, under a bright Mediterranean sky."),
            ["Ancient Greek (1500 - 300 BC)"] = (
                "A man of Classical Athens (5th-4th century BCE), a thoughtful civilian philosopher with a calm expression. He is dressed ONLY in a plain undyed off-white woollen himation draped across one shoulder over a simple linen chiton, in soft folds of cloth, completely unarmoured and unarmed, a teacher and never a soldier (absolutely NO armour, breastplate, cuirass, scale, mail, helmet or weapon on his body). The full-bleed background is the world of Greek philosophy: a sunlit marble colonnaded stoa and the columns of the Academy, an olive grove and cypress around a quiet garden courtyard, papyrus scrolls and a wax tablet on a stone bench, a marble herm and a sundial, robed students conversing in the distance, and the marble temples of the Acropolis on the hill beyond under a calm blue sky.",
                "A woman of Classical Athens (5th-4th century BCE), an elite citizen-wife with a calm, dignified expression. She is dressed ONLY in civilian women's dress: a pleated Ionic linen chiton pinned at the arms and belted at the waist, beneath a draped woollen himation drawn over her head as a veil; her hair is bound into a patterned cloth sakkos with a gold fillet, gold disc earrings and a beaded necklace (absolutely NO armour, helmet or weapon anywhere on her body). The full-bleed background is the world of Greek philosophy: a sunlit colonnaded stoa and the columns of the Academy, an olive grove and cypress around a garden courtyard, scrolls and a wax tablet on a stone bench, a marble herm and a sundial, robed figures in the distance, and the marble temples of the Acropolis under a blue sky."),
            ["Thracian (850 - 0 BC)"] = (
                "A man of the Thracian warrior nobility of the Iron Age eastern Balkans (c. 850 BCE-0), his forearms marked with the traditional geometric tattoos that signal Thracian noble birth, wears a shaggy fox- or bear-skin cap, a brightly patterned woven cloak (the zeira) clasped over a belted tunic, and soft laced hide boots; he is empty-handed and unarmed. The full-bleed background is the Thracian world: rolling oak-forested Balkan hills falling toward the Black Sea coast, mounted Thracian horsemen riding the ridgeline, a grassy tumulus burial mound, glinting gold and silver treasure laid on cloth (an ornate animal-headed rhyton and round phalerae), horses grazing loose, and a hilltop shrine of the Thracian Rider hero beneath a wide sky.",
                "A woman of the Thracian nobility of the Iron Age eastern Balkans (c. 850 BCE-0), her neck and forearms marked with the fine geometric tattoos of a Thracian woman of high birth, wears a long pleated chiton beneath a richly draped, brightly patterned woollen himation mantle; her head is veiled and crowned with a gold diadem, with gold pendant earrings and a heavy gold torc-necklace at her throat. The full-bleed background is the Thracian world: rolling oak-forested Balkan hills falling toward the Black Sea coast, mounted Thracian horsemen riding the ridgeline, a grassy tumulus burial mound, glinting gold and silver treasure laid on cloth (an ornate animal-headed rhyton and round phalerae), horses grazing loose, and a hilltop shrine of the Thracian Rider hero beneath a wide sky."),
            ["Anatolian (1800 - 300 BC)"] = (
                "A man of the Bronze Age Hittite world, his hair gathered at the nape and a neat beard, wearing a long fringed wool tunic belted at the waist. The full-bleed background is the Hittite world packed edge to edge: the cyclopean limestone walls and Lion Gate of Hattusa with sphinx-flanked portals, the rock-cut relief sanctuary of Yazılıkaya carved with long processions of striding gods, a paneled three-man war chariot drawn up nearby, agricultural terracing climbing the windswept Anatolian plateau, herds of cattle grazing across the steppe with herders moving among them, and storm-god stelae bearing horned crowns, under a wide sky with ragged drifting clouds.",
                "A woman of the Bronze Age Hittite world, modestly and fully covered in the manner of Hatti: a long pleated wool robe with loose sleeves falling to the ankles and drawn in at the waist, a tall polos-like crown with a kuressar veil draped over it that flows across her shoulders and back, and a gold diadem with lapis-lazuli and carnelian beads at her throat and bracelets at her wrists. The full-bleed background is the Hittite world packed edge to edge: the cyclopean limestone walls and Lion Gate of Hattusa with sphinx-flanked portals, the rock-cut relief sanctuary of Yazılıkaya carved with processions of gods, a paneled three-man war chariot, terracing on the windswept plateau, herds of cattle with herders, and storm-god stelae bearing horned crowns, under a wide sky with drifting clouds."),
            ["Phoenician (850 - 50 BC)"] = (
                "A man of the seafaring merchant class of Iron Age Tyre, wearing a conical brimless felt cap over oiled curled hair, his beard tightly curled in the eastern manner. He is robed in a long fringed wool tunic dyed deep Tyrian purple with a striped sash at the waist, bronze hoop earrings, a carnelian scarab seal-ring and a faience eye-amulet at his throat. The full-bleed background is the Phoenician world: the walled island city of Tyre with mudbrick towers and the great temple of Melqart, a stone harbour with slipways, beached cedar-hulled merchant galleys and a two-tiered bireme bearing a bronze ram and oxhide-eye prow, heaps of murex shells and shimmering purple-dye vats, glass ampullae and ivory carvings, and the cedar-clad Lebanon hills rising above the blue sea.",
                "A woman of the noble merchant class of Iron Age Tyre, her curled hair bound by a fillet band from which a veil falls over her head, cheeks and shoulders beneath a tall domed headdress. She is enveloped neck to foot in a long wool robe dyed deep Tyrian purple with striped borders, cinched by a knotted girdle, with gold earrings on fine chains, layered bead necklaces, armlets and rings. The full-bleed background is the Phoenician world: the walled island city of Tyre with mudbrick towers and the great temple of Melqart, a stone harbour with slipways, beached cedar-hulled merchant galleys and a two-tiered bireme bearing a bronze ram and oxhide-eye prow, heaps of murex shells and shimmering purple-dye vats, glass ampullae and ivory carvings, and the cedar-clad Lebanon hills above the blue sea."),
            ["Celtic (600 - 50 BC)"] = (
                "A man of the Iron Age Celtic La Tène world — hair lime-washed into stiff spikes, a long drooping moustache and a clean chin — bare-chested with woad-blue swirling tattoos, wearing checkered woven tartan trousers (bracae) and a heavy twisted gold torc at his throat, an iron mail shirt slung over one shoulder. The full-bleed background is the Celtic world: a timber-and-rampart hillfort oppidum on a green hill, thatched round houses, a carnyx war-trumpet, swirling La Tène spiral-and-triskele bronzework, a chariot with two ponies, oak groves, and a stone-carved deity head at a sacred spring.",
                "A woman of the Iron Age Celtic La Tène world, an elite noblewoman dressed as in the Vix and Reinheim graves — hair drawn back beneath a tall felt cap with a draped veil — in a long ankle-length woollen peplos-style gown of checkered twill, pinned at both shoulders with coral-inlaid La Tène spiral fibulae and belted at the waist, a heavy twisted gold torc at her throat, amber and blue-glass bead necklaces, bronze arm-rings and bracelets, a woollen mantle clasped with a fibula. The full-bleed background is the Celtic world: a timber-and-rampart hillfort oppidum on a green hill, thatched round houses, a carnyx war-trumpet, swirling La Tène spiral-and-triskele bronzework, a chariot with two ponies, oak groves, and a stone-carved deity head at a sacred spring."),
            ["Iberian (800 - 50 BC)"] = (
                "A man of the pre-Roman Iberian Spanish Levant, a warrior with hair bound back and worn beneath a fitted sinew cap, dressed in a linen tunic edged with a woven red-and-white border and cinched by a wide bronze belt with a hook clasp. The full-bleed background is the Iberian world: a stone-walled oppidum crowning a dry hilltop above terraced olive groves and wheat fields, mudbrick houses set with painted geometric pottery, the carved limestone Lady of Elche bust and squat stone bull sculptures, esparto-grass slopes, grazing sheep, and a votive sanctuary crowded with small bronze ex-voto figurines.",
                "A woman of the pre-Roman Iberian Spanish Levant, an elite lady in the manner of the Lady of Elche: a long belted tunic and a fringed mantle drawn up as a veil over the head, framed by towering wheel-shaped lateral headdress discs (rodetes) bound by a fillet across the brow, her hair coiled at the sides, and tiers of strung necklaces with amphora-shaped pendants and disc earrings. The full-bleed background is the Iberian world: a stone-walled oppidum crowning a dry hilltop above terraced olive groves and wheat fields, mudbrick houses set with painted geometric pottery, carved limestone busts and squat stone bull sculptures, esparto-grass slopes, grazing sheep, and a votive sanctuary crowded with small bronze ex-voto figurines."),
            ["Carthaginian (800 - 150 BC)"] = (
                "A man of the Carthaginian Punic elite of the western Mediterranean (800-150 BC), an officer wearing a fringed crimson-and-saffron woven tunic with a Tyrian-purple-bordered mantle, gold hoop earrings, a Tanit pendant at his throat, and a bronze-scaled cuirass over linen, his dark hair in oiled ringlets at the temples. The full-bleed background is the Carthaginian world packed edge to edge: the circular cothon war-harbour ringed with ship-sheds and beaked triremes and quinqueremes, the tiered Byrsa citadel, sandstone temples to Baal Hammon and Tanit, a tophet of carved stelae, war elephants with mahouts, amphorae of wine and silver, palms swaying, and the blue Gulf of Tunis under a bright sky.",
                "A woman of the Carthaginian Punic elite of the western Mediterranean (800-150 BC), a noblewoman or priestess wrapped neck-to-foot in a long pleated linen chiton-robe in deep folds beneath a fringed Tyrian-purple-bordered mantle, a fine veil over a diadem in the Egyptianizing Punic style, gold crescent earrings, glass-paste and gold bead necklaces, and a Tanit amulet-case pendant; her hair is bound and draped. The full-bleed background is the Carthaginian world packed edge to edge: the circular cothon war-harbour ringed with ship-sheds and beaked triremes and quinqueremes, the tiered Byrsa citadel, sandstone temples to Baal Hammon and Tanit, a tophet of carved stelae, war elephants with mahouts, amphorae of wine and silver, palms swaying, and the blue Gulf of Tunis under a bright sky."),
            ["Pontic (300 - 50 BC)"] = (
                "A man of the Hellenistic Black Sea coast, a Pontic Greek of the Mithridatic court, wears a fine wool chiton with a draped chlamys cloak pinned at the shoulder by a worked fibula, over the styles of the Mithridatic court: a bronze muscled cuirass with hanging leather pteruges. The full-bleed background is the world of Pontus: the harbor and acropolis of Sinope and Amisos with colonnaded Greek temples and a theater cut into forested hills, the fertile vineyards and chestnut groves of the rugged Paphlagonian coast, fishing boats and grain ships riding the dark Euxine Sea, silver tetradrachm coins bearing a king's portrait, and snow-capped Anatolian mountains rising inland.",
                "A woman of the Hellenistic Black Sea coast, a Pontic Greek noblewoman of the Mithridatic court, wears a fine pleated linen chiton girdled high beneath the bust, with a soft wool himation draped across one shoulder and drawn up as a light veil over her gathered hair; a gold stephane diadem crowns her brow, and she wears gold pendant earrings, a beaded gold necklace and twisted bracelets. The full-bleed background is the world of Pontus: the harbor and acropolis of Sinope and Amisos with colonnaded Greek temples and a theater cut into forested hills, the fertile vineyards and chestnut groves of the rugged Paphlagonian coast, fishing boats and grain ships riding the dark Euxine Sea, silver tetradrachm coins bearing a king's portrait, and snow-capped Anatolian mountains rising inland."),
            ["West Anatolian (0 - 600 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the Roman-era West Anatolian Greek elite of the province of Asia, his hair cut short in the Roman fashion with a neatly trimmed beard, wearing a fine bleached linen tunic under a draped woolen himation pinned at the shoulder with a gold fibula, leather sandals, and a heavy gold signet ring. The full-bleed background is the West Anatolian world: the marble Library of Celsus and the great Temple of Artemis at Ephesus, the terraced Pergamon acropolis with its altar, a colonnaded marble street lined with statues and shops, the harbor of Smyrna crowded with merchant ships, terracotta-roofed villas with mosaic courtyards, and olive groves, vineyards and grazing sheep on sun-baked Aegean hills.",
                "A woman of the Roman-era West Anatolian Greek elite of the province of Asia, her hair dressed in an elaborate updo, wearing an ankle-length fine linen chiton fastened at the shoulders and a draped woolen himation/palla dyed deep cyclamen-purple, adorned in Fayum-portrait fashion with a gilded laurel wreath, a gold-and-emerald necklace, pearl crotalia drop earrings and a gold signet ring. The full-bleed background is the West Anatolian world: the marble Library of Celsus and the great Temple of Artemis at Ephesus, the terraced Pergamon acropolis with its altar, a colonnaded marble street lined with statues and shops, the harbor of Smyrna crowded with merchant ships, terracotta-roofed villas with mosaic courtyards, and olive groves, vineyards and grazing sheep on sun-baked Aegean hills."),
            ["Latin and Etruscan (850 - 150 BC)"] = (
                "A man of Iron Age central Italy, an Etruscan-Italic noble with dark wavy hair and a neatly trimmed pointed beard, wearing a crescent-shaped bronze pectoral cardiophylax over a short bronze-studded linen tunic, with bronze greaves, standing empty-handed. The full-bleed background is the Etruscan world packed edge to edge: a tufa-cut cliffside necropolis of tumulus tombs and carved house-tombs at Cerveteri, terracotta temple roofs crowned with painted antefixes and acroteria, glossy black bucchero pottery and red-figure vases, granulated-gold fibulae and a cast-bronze chimera, and cypress-clad Tuscan hills falling to the Tyrrhenian Sea where merchant ships sail under a bright sky.",
                "A woman of Iron Age central Italy, an Etruscan-Italic noblewoman, her hair in ringlets gathered into a conical tutulus bun, in an ankle-length pleated linen chiton pinned at both shoulders with granulated-gold fibulae and a bordered tebenna mantle, adorned with a gold diadem, baule earrings, a granulated gold pectoral, amber beads and pointed red leather slippers. The full-bleed background is the Etruscan world packed edge to edge: a tufa-cut cliffside necropolis of tumulus tombs and carved house-tombs at Cerveteri, terracotta temple roofs crowned with painted antefixes and acroteria, glossy black bucchero pottery and red-figure vases, granulated-gold fibulae and a cast-bronze chimera, and cypress-clad Tuscan hills falling to the Tyrrhenian Sea where merchant ships sail under a bright sky."),
            ["Moesia Superior (0 - 500 AD)"] = (
                "A man of Moesia Superior on the Danube limes, a Roman provincial legionary, wearing segmented lorica segmentata iron plate over a red tunic, hobnailed caligae, and a knotted balteus belt with apron studs. The full-bleed background is the Moesian world: the legionary fortress of Viminacium with stone walls and a porta praetoria, tiled barracks and a bath-house, the broad grey Danube with patrol liburnian galleys, a milestone road, vineyards on limestone hills, and a Roman tombstone stele beside a temple to Jupiter.",
                "A woman of Moesia Superior on the Danube limes, a Roman provincial matron of standing, wearing a long sleeveless stola suspended by shoulder straps over a fine linen tunica interior, a draped woollen palla shawl pinned with a gilt-bronze fibula and falling from the left shoulder, a provincial Danubian bonnet-style headdress over hair dressed in waves, and pectoral jewellery, gold hoop earrings, a torque, and rings. The full-bleed background is the Moesian world: the legionary fortress of Viminacium with stone walls and a porta praetoria, tiled barracks and a bath-house, the broad grey Danube with patrol liburnian galleys, a milestone road, vineyards on limestone hills, and a Roman tombstone stele beside a temple to Jupiter."),
            ["Eastern Mediterranean (0 - 600 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the Roman-provincial Levantine elite, an adult with a trimmed beard, wearing a long fringed wool tunic and a draped striped mantle dyed with Tyrian purple, a round fibula brooch pinning it at the shoulder, leather sandals, and a heavy gold signet ring and torque. The full-bleed background is the Roman-Levantine world of a caravan city like Palmyra or Apamea: a colonnaded cardo and monumental tetrapylon, a sandstone temple of Bel with Corinthian capitals, mosaic-paved courtyards and a Roman aqueduct, amphorae of wine and olive oil stacked by a busy harbor, laden camel caravans on the trade road, date palms and parched desert hills, and a carved limestone funerary bust set in a tower-tomb under a hot blue sky.",
                "A woman of the Roman-provincial Levantine elite, a noblewoman of a caravan city, wearing a long fine wool tunic beneath a mantle fastened on the left shoulder with a round gold fibula, her head bound in a turban with a central loop and draped in a long veil, over center-parted wavy hair; she wears a jeweled diadem and brow-band with a head-chain, large pendant earrings, several pearl-and-bead necklaces, bracelets, and rings. The full-bleed background is the Roman-Levantine world of a city like Palmyra or Apamea: a colonnaded cardo and tetrapylon, a sandstone temple of Bel with Corinthian capitals, mosaic courtyards and a Roman aqueduct, amphorae by a busy harbor, laden camel caravans, date palms and desert hills, and a carved limestone funerary bust in a tower-tomb under a hot blue sky."),
            ["Germanic (0 - 500 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the Migration-Period Germanic peoples, his long hair pulled into a Suebian knot at the temple and worn with a braided beard, in a knee-length woollen tunic with tablet-woven trim under a riveted mail shirt, leather cross-gartered trousers, an annular brooch and a gilt-bronze belt fitting, standing empty-handed. The full-bleed background is the Germanic world edge to edge: a great timber longhouse with thatched roof and carved gable-beasts amid a misty pine-and-birch forest, a clinker-built oared boat drawn up on a grey fjord shore, standing runestones beside a heaped barrow grave, grazing cattle, and a sacred grove hung with offerings.",
                "A woman of the Migration-Period Germanic peoples, her hair bound up and partly draped under a woven veil, in a long tubular woollen peplos overdress suspended from the shoulders by a pair of gilt-bronze bow brooches linked across the chest by a festoon of glass and amber beads, worn over a long-sleeved linen underdress with a keyhole neckline closed by a small brooch; a strung bead necklace, spiral bronze arm-rings and a tablet-woven belt complete the elite dress. The full-bleed background is the Germanic world edge to edge: a great timber longhouse with thatched roof and carved gable-beasts amid a misty pine-and-birch forest, a clinker-built oared boat drawn up on a grey fjord shore, standing runestones beside a heaped barrow grave, grazing cattle, and a sacred grove hung with offerings."),
            ["Early Slavic (600 - 1200 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the early medieval Eastern European forests, lightly weathered, his hair worn long, in a knee-length belted linen tunic and woollen leg-wrappings with leather lace-up shoes, and a coarse wool cloak pinned at one shoulder by a simple iron brooch. The full-bleed background is the early Slavic world filling the frame: a stockaded gord hillfort of timber ramparts above the river, sunken-floored grubenhaus huts with thatched roofs and rising smoke, hand-thrown Prague-type pottery and bone tools, dugout logboats on the water, stern oak idols of Perun, livestock grazing, and dark birch-and-pine woodland under a pale northern sky.",
                "A woman of the early medieval Eastern European forests, lightly weathered, her hair in braids under a linen kerchief, in a long natural-linen underdress with tapered sleeves worn beneath a striped woollen apron-skirt belted at the waist, with leather lace-up shoes; looped bronze temple rings hang at her headband, glass and amber beads circle her throat, and a small ring brooch fastens her wool wrap. The full-bleed background is the early Slavic world filling the frame: a stockaded gord hillfort of timber ramparts above the river, sunken-floored grubenhaus huts with thatched roofs and rising smoke, hand-thrown Prague-type pottery and bone tools, dugout logboats on the water, stern oak idols of Perun, livestock grazing, and dark birch-and-pine woodland under a pale northern sky."),
            ["North African (0 - 500 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the Roman-era Berber (Amazigh) people of North Africa, with a faint curved facial tattoo on his cheek in the Amazigh tradition, draped in a thick striped woolen burnous over a desert-toned tunic pinned at the shoulder with a bronze fibula. The full-bleed background is the Berber and Roman provincial world: the colonnaded marble streets and theatre of Leptis Magna, a triumphal arch and the harbour of Carthage, mudbrick fortified granaries and tiered ksar villages, a pre-Saharan oasis with date palms, dromedary camels and tethered Barbary horses, mosaic-floored villas, and rolling olive groves above the blue Mediterranean coast.",
                "A woman of the Roman-era Berber (Amazigh) people of North Africa, with a faint Amazigh chin tattoo, her hair bound under a draped woollen headscarf-veil. She wears a large rectangular woollen wrap worn toga-like over a belted undertunic, pinned at both shoulders by a pair of big triangular silver Amazigh fibulae linked by a chest chain, with twisted silver neck-rings and coral-and-silver beads. The full-bleed background is the Berber and Roman provincial world: the colonnaded marble streets and theatre of Leptis Magna, a triumphal arch and the harbour of Carthage, mudbrick fortified granaries and tiered ksar villages, a pre-Saharan oasis with date palms, dromedary camels and tethered Barbary horses, mosaic-floored villas, and rolling olive groves above the blue Mediterranean coast."),
            ["Baltic (BC 200 - 600 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the eastern Baltic Iron Age proto-Balt tribes, his long hair worn loose and his beard trimmed, dressed in a woven woolen tunic and a cloak fastened at the shoulder with a large crossbow-style bronze fibula and ringed penannular brooches, his neck and chest hung with twisted bronze neck-rings and strands of amber beads. The full-bleed background is the Baltic world: a timber-palisaded earthwork hillfort rising above dense pine and oak forest, sunken log dwellings with thatched roofs, dugout fishing canoes drawn up on a misty Baltic shore strewn with raw golden amber, grazing cattle, and a cremation burial field of low mounds.",
                "A woman of the eastern Baltic Iron Age proto-Balt tribes, her hair bound beneath a bronze-spiral chaplet and a coiled headband, dressed in a long linen shift under a dark blue woolen wrap-skirt and a shawl whose hems are sewn with rows of tiny bronze spirals, the shawl pinned across her chest with a crossbow-style bronze fibula and ringed penannular brooches. Her adornments are a twisted bronze neck-ring with hooked terminals, spiral arm-rings and finger-rings, and strands of amber and glass beads. The full-bleed background is the Baltic world: a timber-palisaded earthwork hillfort above dense pine and oak forest, sunken log dwellings with thatched roofs, dugout canoes on a misty Baltic shore strewn with raw golden amber, grazing cattle, and a cremation burial field of low mounds."),
            ["Finno-Ugric Volga (0 - 400 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the Iron Age Volga-Kama forests in a belted woollen tunic and elk-hide leggings under a fur-trimmed cloak, hung with rattling cast-bronze pendants, hollow jingling bells, spiral and waterfowl ornaments and a chest plaque of clasped bronze; his hair worn long. The full-bleed background is the Finno-Ugric Volga world: a palisaded hilltop settlement of timber log dwellings above the wide Kama and Volga rivers, dark spruce-and-birch taiga, smoking bronze-casting hearths and clay moulds, tethered horses and cattle, dugout canoes, fur pelts drying, and earthen burial mounds rich with bronze grave-goods.",
                "A woman of the Iron Age Volga-Kama forests, high-status, in a long belted woollen dress edged with rows of sewn bronze spirals over a linen underdress and a fur-trimmed cloak pinned at the shoulder, a tall birch-bark headdress with a beaded veil and chiming bronze temple-rings, her hair coiled beneath. She wears the noise-jewellery of the Volga Finns: a bronze torc, bead strands, a round breast-plaque, and a fringed apron of rattling waterfowl pendants and bells. The full-bleed background is the Finno-Ugric Volga world: a palisaded hilltop settlement of timber log dwellings above the wide Kama and Volga rivers, dark spruce-and-birch taiga, smoking bronze-casting hearths and clay moulds, tethered horses and cattle, dugout canoes, drying fur pelts, and earthen mounds of bronze grave-goods."),
            ["Saami (0 - 700 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the Iron Age Saami of northern Fennoscandia, dressed in a reindeer-hide tunic and leggings sewn with sinew, a four-winds-style peaked hide hat trimmed with red and yellow woven bands, a pewter-thread-embroidered belt, and curl-toed reindeer-fur boots stuffed with sedge grass; at his neck hang strands of beads and rattling cast-bronze pendants. The full-bleed background is the Saami world: a conical lavvu of poles and hides, a domesticated reindeer herd grazing lichen on snowy tundra, a goahti turf hut, a flat oval shaman's drum painted with sun-symbols, birch-and-pine taiga, a frozen lake, and gákti-pattern reds against pale Arctic light.",
                "A woman of the Iron Age Saami of northern Fennoscandia, dressed in a long belted reindeer-hide dress sewn with sinew, its high collar, cuffs and waist worked with pewter-thread embroidery in red and yellow woven bands, a fringed woven shawl over her shoulders pinned with round bronze brooches; she wears a soft hide-and-woven cap, her hair long beneath it, her chest hung with bead strands and jingling cast-bronze pendants, with curl-toed reindeer-fur boots stuffed with sedge grass. The full-bleed background is the Saami world: a conical lavvu of poles and hides, a domesticated reindeer herd grazing lichen on snowy tundra, a goahti turf hut, a flat oval shaman's drum painted with sun-symbols, birch-and-pine taiga, a frozen lake, and gákti-pattern reds against pale Arctic light."),
            ["Imperial Italy (0 - 550 AD)"] = (
                "A man of Imperial Roman Italy, a legionary in lorica segmentata of overlapping iron plates over a deep-red wool tunic, a military belt with hanging apron studs, and hobnailed caligae sandals; a gladius at his hip. The full-bleed background is the Roman world: the travertine arches of the Colosseum and a Corinthian-columned forum, a triumphal arch and a great aqueduct striding the Campagna, marble temples with brightly painted statues, terracotta-tiled insulae and country villas among dark cypress, terraced vineyards and silvery olive groves, a golden eagle aquila standard raised on its pole, and an oared galley with a furled sail riding the Tiber under a clear Mediterranean sky.",
                "A woman of Imperial Roman Italy, a matron in a long pleated stola of bleached wool belted high beneath the bust over an undertunic, draped in a saffron-bordered palla mantle drawn over the head as a veil; her hair is dressed in matron's curls bound with woolen vittae fillets, with gold drop earrings, a beaded gold necklace, a fibula brooch and signet rings. The full-bleed background is the Roman world: the travertine arches of the Colosseum and a Corinthian-columned forum, a triumphal arch and a great aqueduct striding the Campagna, marble temples with painted statues, terracotta-tiled insulae and villas among dark cypress, terraced vineyards and silvery olive groves, a golden eagle aquila standard, and an oared galley with a furled sail riding the Tiber under a clear Mediterranean sky."),
            ["Aegean (BC 200 - 600 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the Hellenistic Aegean Greek world, draped in a fine bleached-wool himation worn over a belted chiton, fastened with a fibula brooch at the shoulder, a laurel wreath on his brow and a bronze signet ring on his hand. The full-bleed background is the Greek world: a gleaming white marble temple with fluted Ionic columns and a painted pediment on a rocky acropolis, a bustling harbour town of tiled stoas and an agora lined with bronze statues, terraced vineyards and silvery olive groves on sun-baked hillsides, painted black-and-red figure amphorae and a marble herm, and merchant galleys with furled sails and oars riding the deep-blue Aegean.",
                "A woman of the Hellenistic Aegean Greek world, in a fine pleated linen Ionic chiton pinned along the arms, a soft bleached-wool himation draped across her body and drawn up over her head as a veil, her hair dressed in a melon coiffure gathered into a low bun beneath a slender gold stephane, adorned with gold disc earrings, a beaded necklace and a coiled snake bracelet. The full-bleed background is the Greek world: a gleaming white marble temple with fluted Ionic columns and a painted pediment on a rocky acropolis, a bustling harbour town of tiled stoas and an agora lined with bronze statues, terraced vineyards and silvery olive groves on sun-baked hillsides, painted black-and-red figure amphorae and a marble herm, and merchant galleys with furled sails and oars riding the deep-blue Aegean."),
            ["Proto Albanian (500 - 900 AD)"] = (
                "A man of the medieval western Balkans, hair loose to the shoulders, completely BARE-HEADED — no helmet, hood or head-covering. He wears a FULL suit of knight's plate armour — breastplate, pauldrons, vambraces and gauntlets — with chain mail over a plain single-colour surcoat. Armour and surcoat are completely BLANK: NO flag, double-headed eagle, emblem or symbol anywhere. The full-bleed background is the Albanian world: a stone hilltop castle of crenellated towers and a keep above rugged mountains toward the Adriatic, flying one large modern Albanian flag (deep red, black double-headed eagle) from its top — the ONLY flag or eagle anywhere, never on the man; dry-stone battlements, terraced slopes grazed by sheep and goats, and a stone basilica with apses on the karst hill.",
                "A woman of the medieval western Balkans, an elite Komani-Kruja noblewoman in authentic dress: a long linen chemise under a woollen overgown belted with a bronze buckle, a mantle pinned with cast bronze bow-fibulae, hair veiled in a linen head-cloth, with a glass-bead necklace, gilded-bronze Byzantine earrings and bronze rings — but NO double-headed eagle, emblem or symbol anywhere. The full-bleed background is the Albanian world: a stone hilltop castle of crenellated towers and a keep above rugged mountains toward the Adriatic, flying one large modern Albanian flag (deep red, black double-headed eagle) from its top — the ONLY flag or eagle anywhere, never on the woman; dry-stone battlements, terraced slopes grazed by sheep and goats, and a stone basilica with apses on the karst hill."),

        };
}
